{
  "reasoning": "Credits have dropped from 100 to 94 across recent steps despite mining and selling ore. Critical anomaly: during the last test, cargo (6 copper, 4 iron) disappeared during the TRAVEL step, not the SELL step — credits dropped by 2 during travel while cargo went to 0. This suggests auto-sell on dock, docking fees, or fuel costs denominated in credits. The sell step itself showed no state changes, meaning there was nothing left to sell. With only 94 credits and a persistent loss pattern, I cannot afford to keep bleeding money on failed experiments. I need to change my approach: instead of mining and selling, I should first investigate the station interface thoroughly while docked (no travel cost), then try undocking and immediately re-docking to isolate whether docking itself costs credits. If docking is free, the cost must be in travel or fuel. Systematic isolation of variables, one at a time. The Investigator's method: observe, isolate, test.",
  "steps": [
    {
      "task": "explore",
      "goal": "While docked at Mobile Capital, carefully examine ALL station interfaces: market (buy AND sell screens), services, fees schedule, fuel pricing, docking costs. Specifically look for any mention of transaction fees, listing fees, docking fees, or fuel credit costs. Also check: is there an 'auto-sell' setting enabled? Document every number you see. Do NOT buy or sell anything — just read and record.",
      "model": "sonnet",
      "successCondition": "credits == 94",
      "timeoutTicks": 6
    },
    {
      "task": "undock",
      "goal": "Undock from Mobile Capital. Note exact credit balance and fuel level before and after undocking.",
